# Leader Failover Demonstration
# Scenario: replica1 (Leader) crashes unexpectedly. After a heartbeat timeout, replica2 and replica3 immediately hold an election and agree upon a new term to protect cluster integrity.

[replica1] 2026/04/20 10:32:15 term=2 state=LEADER event=heartbeat_sent peers=2
[replica2] 2026/04/20 10:32:15 term=2 state=FOLLOWER event=heartbeat_received from=replica1
[replica3] 2026/04/20 10:32:15 term=2 state=FOLLOWER event=heartbeat_received from=replica1
# ---> (replica1 container crashes/stops responding)
[replica2] 2026/04/20 10:32:16 term=3 state=CANDIDATE event=election_started
[replica2] 2026/04/20 10:32:16 term=3 state=CANDIDATE event=vote_requested peers=1
[replica3] 2026/04/20 10:32:16 term=3 state=FOLLOWER event=vote_granted candidate=replica2
[replica2] 2026/04/20 10:32:16 term=3 state=LEADER event=election_won votes=2
[replica2] 2026/04/20 10:32:16 term=3 state=LEADER event=heartbeat_sent peers=1
[replica3] 2026/04/20 10:32:16 term=3 state=FOLLOWER event=heartbeat_received from=replica2
